tspan.tspan: The goal of the tutorial is to enable modellers to perform simple operations to evaluate their forecasts using the pyCSEP toolkit. This includes downloading and plotting earthquake catalogue data, filtering a catalogue to testing regions, learning about CSEP standards and formats, plotting forecasts, and performing standard CSEP forecast consDistency and comparison tests.

PyCSEP is an open-source community-developed python library that provides tools for (1) evaluating probabilistic earthquake forecasts, (2) working with earthquake catalogues in this context, and (3) creating visualisations.tasdt
